    TimingI, java.io.Serializable

    public class SignalData<T extends java.io.Serializable>
extends AbstractSignalData
implements java.io.Serializable
    The class SignalData implements a simple signal data, combining a measure and its time stamping information inherited from TimedEntity.

    Description

    A signal is the measure of a physical phenomena over time. Given the discrete nature of computers, signals are known only at discrete points in time using measures. An instance of SignalData represents one of these timed measures, composed of a value of a generic type T and a measurement unit of type MeasurementUnit (value which can be MeasurementUnit.RAW when there is no actual unit).
